1
00:00:23,565 --> 00:00:26,898
(CHILD SINGING HÄNSCHEN KLEIN)

2
00:01:04,690 --> 00:01:06,314
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

3
00:01:24,524 --> 00:01:25,523
(GUNS FIRING)

4
00:01:25,774 --> 00:01:27,814
(MARCHING BAND PLAYING)

5
00:01:35,607 --> 00:01:37,356
(HÄNSCHEN KLEIN RESUMES)

6
00:01:55,982 --> 00:01:57,731
(BRASS FANFARE PLAYING)

7
00:02:09,399 --> 00:02:11,106
(HÄNSCHEN KLEIN RESUMES)

8
00:02:31,774 --> 00:02:33,564
(MARCHING BAND PLAYING)

9
00:03:35,024 --> 00:03:36,064
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

10
00:04:08,190 --> 00:04:10,314
(GUNS FIRING)

11
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:34,689
(SHELL FIRING)

12
00:04:47,274 --> 00:04:50,981
This is Regimental Headquarters
calling Corporal Steiner.

13
00:04:51,399 --> 00:04:52,731
(SHELLS FIRING)

14
00:04:56,732 --> 00:04:58,064
Can you pick me up, Steiner?

15
00:05:00,065 --> 00:05:01,523
Steiner, can you hear me?

16
00:05:02,524 --> 00:05:03,731
Steiner.

17
00:05:17,732 --> 00:05:19,773
(SHELLS FIRING INTERMITTENTLY)

18
00:05:45,232 --> 00:05:46,564
(DISTANT EXPLOSION)

19
00:05:50,024 --> 00:05:51,856
(SHELLING CONTINUES)

20
00:06:16,899 --> 00:06:18,439
(GRUNTING)

21
00:06:53,815 --> 00:06:55,398
(MAN SPEAKING RUSSIAN ON PHONE)

22
00:06:58,482 --> 00:07:00,189
(EXPLOSIONS CONTINUE IN DISTANCE)

23
00:07:27,815 --> 00:07:29,064
(MIMICS GUNSHOT)

24
00:07:37,107 --> 00:07:38,773
(SOLDIER EXCLAIMING IN RUSSIAN)

25
00:07:38,899 --> 00:07:40,356
(HORSE NEIGHING)

26
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:41,981
(MEN SCREAMING)

27
00:07:45,232 --> 00:07:46,689
(MACHINE GUNS FIRING)

28
00:08:06,899 --> 00:08:08,731
- Good kill!
- KERN: Beautiful.

29
00:08:10,024 --> 00:08:11,773
Look, my new weapon.

30
00:08:13,524 --> 00:08:15,648
Get one for yourself. Some ammunition.

31
00:08:16,565 --> 00:08:18,689
- Give him a hand.
- Of course.

32
00:08:20,149 --> 00:08:21,189
Look at that!

33
00:08:23,065 --> 00:08:26,689
STEINER: Nothing we haven't seen before.
ANSELM: Steiner.

34
00:08:26,774 --> 00:08:30,981
Look what I found running around
in the back. A little Russian fledgling.

35
00:08:37,524 --> 00:08:38,898
Put it down.

36
00:08:46,732 --> 00:08:49,731
(PLAYING HARMONICA)

37
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:05,064
STEINER: Quickly!

38
00:09:07,732 --> 00:09:08,773
We go.

39
00:09:10,565 --> 00:09:15,564
See if you can get Meyer. Tell him we'll
need transportation from checkpoint seven.

40
00:09:15,982 --> 00:09:17,731
ANSELM: Right, sir.

41
00:09:19,482 --> 00:09:20,814
Bring him with us.

42
00:09:20,899 --> 00:09:24,064
- (ENGINE STRUGGLING)
- Push, push, push, push, push!

43
00:09:25,274 --> 00:09:27,773
Come on, come on! Quickly!

44
00:09:32,190 --> 00:09:33,773
All right, stop.

45
00:09:44,190 --> 00:09:45,939
(STRANSKY URINATING)

46
00:09:57,982 --> 00:09:59,898
This damned country!

47
00:10:01,232 --> 00:10:03,731
Once it was a new adventure,

48
00:10:05,149 --> 00:10:09,523
but I have a feeling that one of these days,
this land will swallow us up.

49
00:10:10,649 --> 00:10:12,523
Captain Stransky, sir.

50
00:10:13,732 --> 00:10:16,814
- Colonel Brandt. You're welcome.
- Thank you, sir.

51
00:10:20,732 --> 00:10:23,439
BRANDT: This is my adjutant, Captain Kiesel.

52
00:10:24,315 --> 00:10:25,981
Captain, how are you?

53
00:10:26,065 --> 00:10:29,273
Thank you for asking, Captain.
I feel terrible. I've got diarrhoea.

54
00:10:29,357 --> 00:10:30,648
How are you?

55
00:10:30,732 --> 00:10:34,023
You should meet your own adjutant.
Lieutenant Triebig.

56
00:10:34,107 --> 00:10:35,731
He's also a new arrival.

57
00:10:35,815 --> 00:10:37,981
Won't you join us in a glass of wine?

58
00:10:38,065 --> 00:10:40,939
STRANSKY: Oh, that's very kind of you, sir.
Take my coat, please.

59
00:10:41,399 --> 00:10:43,106
ORDERLY: Yes, sir.
STRANSKY: Hmm.

60
00:10:43,190 --> 00:10:44,648
(MAN HUMMING)

61
00:10:46,732 --> 00:10:52,731
My respects, Colonel. A 1 937 Mosel
in the southernmost corner of Russia.

62
00:10:54,399 --> 00:10:55,731
Remarkable!

63
00:10:55,815 --> 00:11:00,981
A bottle of Mosel is no more out of place
in this region than we are ourselves.

64
00:11:02,565 --> 00:11:03,606
Your health, gentlemen.

65
00:11:03,690 --> 00:11:05,856
I'm not going to drink to my health.

66
00:11:05,940 --> 00:11:08,064
It's not worth drinking to.

67
00:11:09,899 --> 00:11:11,523
To the end of the war?

68
00:11:20,649 --> 00:11:26,814
Colonel, why does our presence here
strike you as so absurd?

69
00:11:26,899 --> 00:11:30,731
Captain, why did you ask to be
relieved from duty in France?

70
00:11:31,524 --> 00:11:33,523
I want to get the Iron Cross.

71
00:11:35,690 --> 00:11:37,273
We could give you one of mine.

72
00:11:37,357 --> 00:11:40,731
- (LAUGHS) No, no, I'm just joking.
- (THUNDER RUMBLING)

73
00:11:40,815 --> 00:11:45,148
Actually it's exactly what my
commanding officer in France asked me.

74
00:11:45,232 --> 00:11:47,273
"I can't stop you, " he said.

75
00:11:47,357 --> 00:11:50,148
"Since I'm convinced that
without you the Eastern Front

76
00:11:50,232 --> 00:11:52,314
"would collapse in a matter of days.

77
00:11:52,399 --> 00:11:55,773
"Go ahead, you heroic horse's ass. "

78
00:11:55,857 --> 00:11:56,856
(LARGE EXPLOSION)

79
00:12:02,690 --> 00:12:06,398
"Heroic horse's ass. " His exact words.

80
00:12:07,815 --> 00:12:10,439
I withdraw my toast to the end of the war.

81
00:12:11,065 --> 00:12:13,731
To heroic horse's asses everywhere.

82
00:12:13,815 --> 00:12:15,773
To the patient foolish.

83
00:12:15,857 --> 00:12:21,231
Colonel, I would like to make something
quite clear to Captain Kiesel.

84
00:12:22,024 --> 00:12:28,273
I volunteered for this campaign because
I feel that men of quality are needed here.

85
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:34,939
It is time to destroy the myth
of Russian invincibility.

86
00:12:35,024 --> 00:12:36,898
Just how do we do that?

87
00:12:37,399 --> 00:12:43,064
Bolstering morale, punishing those
who are insubordinate and rebellious.

88
00:12:43,149 --> 00:12:45,939
Instilling a new respect for ranking officers.

89
00:12:46,024 --> 00:12:49,064
Low morale goes hand in hand
with defeat after defeat

90
00:12:49,149 --> 00:12:50,939
followed by impending defeat.

91
00:12:51,024 --> 00:12:53,648
Now you are new to our Russian front,

92
00:12:53,732 --> 00:12:58,148
so I don't blame you
for talking like a horse's ass.

93
00:12:58,232 --> 00:12:59,439
(CHUCKLING)

94
00:13:03,399 --> 00:13:07,356
Of course, sir, I'm not familiar
with the Russian front yet,

95
00:13:07,440 --> 00:13:13,314
but I firmly don't believe that the ideals
of the German soldier even...

96
00:13:13,399 --> 00:13:17,314
The German soldier no longer has any ideals.

97
00:13:17,399 --> 00:13:20,856
He's not fighting for the culture of the West,

98
00:13:20,940 --> 00:13:23,856
not for one form of government that he wants,

99
00:13:23,940 --> 00:13:25,564
and not for the stinking party.

100
00:13:25,649 --> 00:13:29,564
He's fighting for his life. God bless him.

101
00:13:29,649 --> 00:13:35,398
Well, sir, I am a soldier, and as a soldier,
I feel it is my duty to subordinate

102
00:13:35,482 --> 00:13:41,564
my own ideas to the principles of my country,
right or wrong.

103
00:13:42,399 --> 00:13:44,523
Colonel Brandt, Lieutenant Meyer, sir.

104
00:13:44,607 --> 00:13:45,773
Ah. (CLEARS THROAT)

105
00:13:48,732 --> 00:13:51,189
- Yes?
- Steiner's on his way back.

106
00:13:51,274 --> 00:13:54,398
- What sort of shape are they in?
- The usual!

107
00:13:54,482 --> 00:13:56,189
BRANDT: Very well, I see.

108
00:13:56,274 --> 00:13:58,648
I want a briefing as soon as they're rested.

109
00:13:58,732 --> 00:14:02,939
- Yes, sir.
- And, Meyer, Captain Stransky is here.

110
00:14:03,024 --> 00:14:05,439
See that he is informed of our situation.

111
00:14:05,565 --> 00:14:06,773
Yes, sir.

112
00:14:08,899 --> 00:14:10,273
(SHELL WHISTLING)

113
00:14:10,399 --> 00:14:11,648
(SHELL EXPLODING)

114
00:14:11,732 --> 00:14:12,939
(SIGHS)

115
00:14:13,649 --> 00:14:16,064
- Steiner's back.
- Of course.

116
00:14:19,107 --> 00:14:20,439
Who's Steiner?

117
00:14:21,524 --> 00:14:24,731
To you, in some ways, he could be a problem.

118
00:14:24,815 --> 00:14:27,273
But he's a first-rate soldier.

119
00:14:27,357 --> 00:14:30,189
So, we look the other way.

120
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:33,773
Anything to add to that, Kiesel?

121
00:14:36,065 --> 00:14:38,773
Steiner is a myth.

122
00:14:40,607 --> 00:14:43,981
But men like him are our last hope.

123
00:14:45,232 --> 00:14:49,189
And in that sense,
he's truly a very dangerous man.

124
00:14:56,899 --> 00:14:58,523
Well, I will see.

125
00:14:59,524 --> 00:15:01,898
Colonel, with your permission.

126
00:15:16,940 --> 00:15:21,148
Well, what do you think of our new captain?

127
00:15:21,232 --> 00:15:24,148
I feel he thinks he is on
some kind of special mission,

128
00:15:24,232 --> 00:15:28,106
that is, to achieve spiritual domination
of his battalion,

129
00:15:28,940 --> 00:15:35,689
thereby symbolising the purity
of the great German Wehrmacht itself.

130
00:15:37,149 --> 00:15:38,689
(MEN SCREAMING)

131
00:15:44,065 --> 00:15:46,189
Even when going down in defeat.

132
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:49,481
(SCREAMING)

133
00:16:04,732 --> 00:16:08,648
If they're the last of us, Stransky and Steiner,
then God help us.

134
00:16:16,190 --> 00:16:17,689
SOLDIER: Medic!

135
00:16:18,774 --> 00:16:20,481
Medic! Medic!

136
00:16:23,232 --> 00:16:26,231
Captain Stransky,
welcome to the second platoon.

137
00:16:28,357 --> 00:16:30,481
- Lieutenant.
- Meyer, Captain.

138
00:16:31,357 --> 00:16:33,023
I am to show you to your quarters,

139
00:16:33,524 --> 00:16:35,314
brief you on our current situation.

140
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:36,439
(EXPLODING)

141
00:16:36,690 --> 00:16:37,731
(MAN SCREAMING)

142
00:16:38,565 --> 00:16:41,939
- Where's my bunker?
- Down there, in front of the factory, sir.

143
00:16:42,024 --> 00:16:45,064
- The second platoon is guarding your post.
- Where are they?

144
00:16:45,149 --> 00:16:48,314
They're just returning
from reconnaissance, sir.

145
00:16:48,399 --> 00:16:51,023
STRANSKY: Who's in charge of it?
MEYER: Corporal Steiner, sir.

146
00:16:51,107 --> 00:16:52,731
Oh.

147
00:16:52,815 --> 00:16:55,273
What is so special
about this Corporal Steiner?

148
00:16:55,357 --> 00:16:59,314
MEYER: Early in the Novorossiysk attack,
Corporal Steiner saved Colonel Brandt's life.

149
00:16:59,399 --> 00:17:00,981
- Ah!
- And mine, too.

150
00:17:01,065 --> 00:17:02,939
STRANSKY: Interesting.

151
00:17:11,190 --> 00:17:12,814
Corporal Steiner!

152
00:17:14,649 --> 00:17:18,564
I'm Captain Stransky.
I'm your new commander here.

153
00:17:20,024 --> 00:17:21,273
Yes, sir.

154
00:17:24,232 --> 00:17:25,273
Who's this?

155
00:17:25,357 --> 00:17:27,148
STEINER: Corporal Schnurrbart, sir.

156
00:17:27,232 --> 00:17:28,856
And the other one?

157
00:17:28,940 --> 00:17:31,273
That is a Russian prisoner, sir.

158
00:17:32,565 --> 00:17:37,689
You know as well as I do that there are orders
that no Russian prisoners are to be taken.

159
00:17:38,565 --> 00:17:40,106
Get rid of him.

160
00:17:40,565 --> 00:17:41,648
How, sir?

161
00:17:41,940 --> 00:17:44,606
Well, shoot him!

162
00:17:45,274 --> 00:17:47,023
You shoot him, sir.

163
00:17:52,274 --> 00:17:55,773
I will. On the spot.

164
00:17:57,440 --> 00:17:58,648
And then I'll deal with you.

165
00:18:03,315 --> 00:18:08,398
No need. I'll see that it's taken care of, sir.

166
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:25,564
I want to see you in my bunker. One hour.

167
00:18:26,732 --> 00:18:28,314
With your full report.

168
00:18:28,690 --> 00:18:30,564
- Clear?
- Of course, sir.

169
00:18:41,024 --> 00:18:42,648
(SHELL EXPLODING)

170
00:18:53,065 --> 00:18:54,689
(SOLDIERS CHATTERING)

171
00:18:58,065 --> 00:18:59,689
(STEINER GROANS)

172
00:19:03,065 --> 00:19:07,189
- You already drank both the vodka.
- I'm using it for the cooking.

173
00:19:27,065 --> 00:19:28,939
(SHELL EXPLODES)

174
00:20:24,315 --> 00:20:25,523
(SIGHS)

175
00:20:30,399 --> 00:20:31,648
Oh, shit.

176
00:20:42,899 --> 00:20:45,731
- Corporal Steiner?
- I'm Lily Marlene.

177
00:20:49,857 --> 00:20:51,398
Come here, son.

178
00:20:55,232 --> 00:20:56,481
Steiner!

179
00:20:58,232 --> 00:21:01,481
I want to show you
what our new army looks like.

180
00:21:09,857 --> 00:21:12,689
- What's your name, son?
- Private Dietz, sir.

181
00:21:12,774 --> 00:21:15,023
They're sending us babies now.

182
00:21:15,815 --> 00:21:17,231
Hello, child.

183
00:21:17,315 --> 00:21:18,814
Private Dietz.

184
00:21:22,232 --> 00:21:23,439
How long have you been soldiering?

185
00:21:23,982 --> 00:21:26,231
Six weeks, sir. I volunteered, sir.

186
00:21:26,565 --> 00:21:28,731
Don't volunteer for anything around here.

187
00:21:29,107 --> 00:21:32,106
Just keep your eye on Krüger here,
and myself.

188
00:21:32,190 --> 00:21:36,064
Do exactly as we say or you'll be wearing
boots up your ass for a long time.

189
00:21:36,149 --> 00:21:37,606
- Clear?
- Yes, sir!

190
00:21:38,774 --> 00:21:41,523
- And don't call me sir.
- Excuse me.

191
00:21:43,982 --> 00:21:46,064
Go with this foul-smelling one over here.

192
00:21:46,149 --> 00:21:48,064
Put him in Schiller's bunk.

193
00:21:53,857 --> 00:22:00,231
Kern, see if you can find a jacket or a blanket,

194
00:22:00,899 --> 00:22:02,523
something for the boy.

195
00:22:02,607 --> 00:22:04,981
Get Schiller's jacket.
He must have something over there.

196
00:22:05,065 --> 00:22:07,189
Yes, sir! Oh, excuse me.

197
00:22:08,107 --> 00:22:10,064
STRANSKY: Stand at ease.

198
00:22:10,565 --> 00:22:11,606
Thank you, sir.

199
00:22:12,065 --> 00:22:13,564
(CHATTER ON RADIO)

200
00:22:13,857 --> 00:22:15,939
- My report.
- Thank you.

201
00:22:18,690 --> 00:22:23,939
I regret the incident this afternoon, Corporal.

202
00:22:24,024 --> 00:22:26,064
But orders are orders.

203
00:22:26,149 --> 00:22:31,148
We have enough trouble with the feeding
of our own troops without taking prisoners.

204
00:22:32,899 --> 00:22:35,398
Anyway, it's very bad for security.

205
00:22:37,399 --> 00:22:39,981
I've read your preliminary report,

206
00:22:40,065 --> 00:22:43,856
and it gives me great pleasure
to inform you that

207
00:22:43,940 --> 00:22:46,731
Colonel Brandt and I have
agreed to recommend you

208
00:22:46,815 --> 00:22:51,439
for promotion to Senior Sergeant,
effective at once.

209
00:22:58,399 --> 00:23:01,648
Your promotion doesn't seem to have
made much of an impression.

210
00:23:01,732 --> 00:23:02,773
No, it doesn't.

211
00:23:08,232 --> 00:23:09,564
All right.

212
00:23:10,940 --> 00:23:13,773
I've read your report. Anything to add to this?

213
00:23:14,732 --> 00:23:17,731
Russians, sir. We should be
hearing from them very soon, sir.

214
00:23:17,815 --> 00:23:20,231
- An offensive?
- Yes, I should think so, sir.

215
00:23:20,315 --> 00:23:21,814
- Starting when?
- Soon.

216
00:23:26,607 --> 00:23:29,481
- What about your platoon?
- Two killed, one missing.

217
00:23:29,565 --> 00:23:31,314
Two killed, how?

218
00:23:33,149 --> 00:23:37,731
Bullets. Mortar fire. Artillery.
Heavy salvos. Bad luck.

219
00:23:38,149 --> 00:23:42,273
Terminal syphilis. The usual things, Captain.

220
00:23:43,399 --> 00:23:46,856
The missing man,
did you look for him, Steiner?

221
00:23:46,940 --> 00:23:48,231
- No, sir.
- Why not?

222
00:23:48,815 --> 00:23:53,481
I felt that it would be irresponsible of me
to risk the safety of the entire platoon

223
00:23:53,565 --> 00:23:54,773
for the sake of one man.

224
00:23:58,774 --> 00:24:00,273
You felt what?

225
00:24:04,649 --> 00:24:10,981
A non-commissioned officer does not permit
a missing man in such a case, in any case!

226
00:24:11,065 --> 00:24:12,689
I'll try to do better next time, sir.

227
00:24:12,774 --> 00:24:15,273
- I'd like to have that in writing.
- If you wish.

228
00:24:19,899 --> 00:24:22,814
You know, Corporal... Sergeant,

229
00:24:24,065 --> 00:24:28,231
I have a feeling you somewhat
overestimate your importance.

230
00:24:29,232 --> 00:24:33,564
At the moment,
I am free of any such illusions, sir.

231
00:24:36,357 --> 00:24:40,856
Well, may I suggest to you that you do not
underestimate your present company.

232
00:24:40,940 --> 00:24:47,564
Everything you are and may become
is dependent upon this present company.

233
00:24:48,565 --> 00:24:50,314
No, I will not forget that, sir.

234
00:24:51,607 --> 00:24:56,148
But I may add that a man is generally
what he feels himself to be.

235
00:25:02,107 --> 00:25:05,814
Of course.

236
00:25:07,274 --> 00:25:08,898
You're dismissed.

237
00:25:12,274 --> 00:25:14,314
I shall be back soon, sir.

238
00:25:15,065 --> 00:25:16,106
Is that a salute?

239
00:25:19,565 --> 00:25:20,648
Yes, sir.

240
00:25:22,857 --> 00:25:25,064
- Triebig.
- Yes, sir.

241
00:25:25,899 --> 00:25:30,314
MEYER: You must be careful, Steiner.
He's taken a strong dislike to you.

242
00:25:30,399 --> 00:25:31,898
STEINER: I'll survive.

243
00:25:31,982 --> 00:25:34,481
MEYER: You're not dealing with
just another Nazi Party type.

244
00:25:37,399 --> 00:25:40,898
This one is pure Prussian
military aristocracy and rich.

245
00:25:46,232 --> 00:25:48,523
Hey, why are you bringing in the apples?

246
00:25:48,607 --> 00:25:50,273
To eat, you overgrown idiot.

247
00:25:50,940 --> 00:25:52,523
You know the ruling classes?

