(MEN GRUNTING)

502
00:45:32,149 --> 00:45:33,481
MAN: Fire!

503
00:45:33,774 --> 00:45:35,106
(GRUNTING)

504
00:45:39,565 --> 00:45:41,231
(SCREAMING)

505
00:45:56,274 --> 00:45:58,856
- Captain Stransky.
- Where's your counterattack?

506
00:45:58,940 --> 00:46:01,439
We are attacking! We are defending!

507
00:46:01,899 --> 00:46:03,189
We're counterattacking!

508
00:46:14,149 --> 00:46:17,064
I'm wounded, sir. But I continue.

509
00:46:17,149 --> 00:46:19,189
I know my duty, sir. Don't worry.

510
00:46:19,940 --> 00:46:21,689
But I need ammunition!

511
00:46:38,190 --> 00:46:39,398
MAN: Lieutenant Meyer!

512
00:46:48,232 --> 00:46:50,189
Hollerbach! We must cover Steiner!

513
00:47:41,357 --> 00:47:42,731
Look at me.

514
00:47:50,732 --> 00:47:52,523
Follow the light with your eyes.

515
00:48:02,857 --> 00:48:03,856
Very good.

516
00:48:07,524 --> 00:48:09,856
That's it. Now look at me again.

517
00:48:17,274 --> 00:48:18,439
Sergeant!

518
00:48:21,399 --> 00:48:22,398
All right.

519
00:48:31,899 --> 00:48:33,648
Did you sleep well?

520
00:48:35,690 --> 00:48:37,064
Reasonably.

521
00:48:42,315 --> 00:48:43,314
Smell?

522
00:48:43,815 --> 00:48:45,023
(SNIFFS)

523
00:48:46,774 --> 00:48:47,981
Nothing.

524
00:48:48,065 --> 00:48:49,814
Any sense of taste?

525
00:48:59,024 --> 00:49:00,356
lmproving.

526
00:49:03,857 --> 00:49:05,564
Quite usual in concussion.

527
00:49:07,482 --> 00:49:09,898
You've been like this for a week.

528
00:49:10,732 --> 00:49:12,731
They should return soon.

529
00:49:13,732 --> 00:49:17,398
Your records indicate multiple wounds
over the last few years.

530
00:49:17,482 --> 00:49:19,273
Any residual effects?

531
00:49:22,357 --> 00:49:23,689
Headaches.

532
00:49:25,565 --> 00:49:27,106
Blurred vision.

533
00:49:28,399 --> 00:49:35,231
I can't urinate out of my left ear any longer,
but otherwise I feel rather well.

534
00:49:38,940 --> 00:49:41,981
The doctors recommend that you stay with us
for another three weeks

535
00:49:42,065 --> 00:49:44,564
until they've completed your tests.

536
00:49:45,899 --> 00:49:48,939
Then they recommend home leave.

537
00:49:52,232 --> 00:49:53,356
Home.

538
00:50:02,065 --> 00:50:04,106
(LIVELY INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

539
00:50:28,940 --> 00:50:30,898
(MUSIC BECOMES DISTANT)

540
00:50:33,024 --> 00:50:34,689
(MAN'S LAUGHTER ECHOING)

541
00:50:54,815 --> 00:50:57,856
Schnurrbart? Schnurrbart?

542
00:51:10,232 --> 00:51:12,814
MAN: Attention! General Von Hessel!

543
00:51:15,690 --> 00:51:17,564
(ALL SINGING IN GERMAN)

544
00:51:44,399 --> 00:51:47,981
Hello, soldier? How are you?
Tell me, how do you feel?

545
00:51:49,357 --> 00:51:51,106
This man has severe concussion, sir.

546
00:51:52,399 --> 00:51:54,523
He's been highly decorated.

547
00:52:17,857 --> 00:52:22,106
I want 65% of these men
returned to active duty in three days.

548
00:52:23,732 --> 00:52:25,523
Ah, food!

549
00:52:30,024 --> 00:52:31,148
VON HESSEL: Delicious!

550
00:52:31,232 --> 00:52:34,898
MAN: Take the pig, the meat and the wine
into the private dining room.

551
00:52:35,065 --> 00:52:40,231
Come! Eat! Eat, eat, everybody! Everybody!

552
00:52:41,815 --> 00:52:43,148
Vegetables are good for you.

553
00:52:43,232 --> 00:52:45,481
They're with the compliments
of the High Command.

554
00:52:48,024 --> 00:52:49,481
(SOLDIERS SINGING DISTANTLY)

555
00:52:56,607 --> 00:52:58,231
(SINGING ECHOING CHAOTICALLY)

556
00:53:11,232 --> 00:53:12,564
(ECHOING GUNFIRE)

557
00:53:17,232 --> 00:53:18,731
(DISTANT CHANTING)

558
00:53:22,815 --> 00:53:25,064
(MAN DELIVERING SPEECH)

559
00:53:38,732 --> 00:53:40,689
(INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC RESUMES)

560
00:53:52,232 --> 00:53:55,564
STEINER: Everybody looks
like someone else around here.

561
00:53:57,190 --> 00:53:59,106
Did I have a bad spell?

562
00:53:59,940 --> 00:54:03,814
Yeah, you were very violent.

563
00:54:04,607 --> 00:54:05,648
Violent?

564
00:54:05,732 --> 00:54:08,606
Violence should stop. It must stop.

565
00:54:11,899 --> 00:54:14,023
You say the violence must stop?

566
00:54:16,024 --> 00:54:17,023
(CHUCKLES)

567
00:54:20,232 --> 00:54:21,856
(SHOUTING)

568
00:54:30,899 --> 00:54:32,398
(SOLDIERS LAUGHING)

569
00:54:36,815 --> 00:54:38,523
(VIOLIN PLAYING WALTZ MUSIC)

570
00:54:41,274 --> 00:54:43,023
Oh, no, I'm on duty.

571
00:54:43,232 --> 00:54:44,981
- Have a drink.
- No, I couldn't.

572
00:54:45,065 --> 00:54:46,856
They'll throw me out.

573
00:54:53,065 --> 00:54:54,481
Do you dance?

574
00:54:55,815 --> 00:54:57,148
(CHUCKLING)

575
00:54:57,232 --> 00:55:01,398
Hold my bottle. I'll hold your waist.

576
00:55:03,982 --> 00:55:05,439
And we dance.

577
00:55:07,399 --> 00:55:11,023
Listen, this is ridiculous.

578
00:55:14,940 --> 00:55:16,898
It's nice.

579
00:55:17,690 --> 00:55:19,523
(BOTH LAUGHING)

580
00:55:32,815 --> 00:55:34,148
Schnurrbart!

581
00:55:35,024 --> 00:55:36,023
Rolf?

582
00:55:36,232 --> 00:55:38,731
What the hell are you doing here? Lost?

583
00:55:38,857 --> 00:55:40,064
No such luck, Rolf.

584
00:55:40,732 --> 00:55:43,689
I got it in the leg same time
you got it in the head.

585
00:55:43,899 --> 00:55:45,023
Schnurrbart!

586
00:55:45,107 --> 00:55:46,481
My vacation's over.

587
00:55:46,899 --> 00:55:49,606
It's back to the bad side
of old mother Russia.

588
00:55:50,440 --> 00:55:52,564
They took us all from our hospital.

589
00:55:53,107 --> 00:55:56,731
It looks like we're picking up
some of your boys as well.

590
00:55:57,107 --> 00:55:59,148
You want to come along
or are you doing all right?

591
00:56:02,524 --> 00:56:04,356
Attention, men! Prepare to leave.

592
00:56:06,899 --> 00:56:10,148
Corporal! Hold this truck.

593
00:56:10,232 --> 00:56:11,981
What the hell are you talking about?

594
00:56:12,524 --> 00:56:14,481
That's an order, God damn it!

595
00:56:20,274 --> 00:56:21,981
- Rolf?
- What?

596
00:56:22,065 --> 00:56:23,981
- What is it?
- What?

597
00:56:26,274 --> 00:56:27,481
What's the matter?

598
00:56:30,107 --> 00:56:31,648
I'm going back.

599
00:56:36,274 --> 00:56:38,648
I thought you were going back home.

600
00:56:41,399 --> 00:56:42,398
I have no home.

601
00:56:43,815 --> 00:56:45,481
My home.

602
00:56:47,732 --> 00:56:48,814
Our home.

603
00:57:14,065 --> 00:57:16,273
Do you love the war so much?

604
00:57:37,232 --> 00:57:41,523
Is that...
Is that what's wrong with you, Steiner?

605
00:57:50,399 --> 00:57:52,523
Or are you afraid of what
you will be without it?

606
00:58:15,815 --> 00:58:16,814
Long live Germany.

607
00:58:32,315 --> 00:58:33,814
I said to hold it, right?

608
00:58:33,899 --> 00:58:35,564
Steiner, I didn't mean it. You're crazy!

609
00:58:35,649 --> 00:58:36,898
Schnurrbart.

610
00:59:16,690 --> 00:59:17,856
Rolf!

611
00:59:22,399 --> 00:59:24,023
Son of a bitch!

612
00:59:25,065 --> 00:59:26,898
- Schnurrbart!
- Hello, Kern!

613
00:59:30,399 --> 00:59:32,731
- Hello, Hartwig.
- Hello, Sergeant.

614
00:59:33,024 --> 00:59:34,564
- Hartwig!
- Schnurrbart, how are you?

615
00:59:34,690 --> 00:59:36,648
Caught with your
pants down again, huh?

616
00:59:36,732 --> 00:59:37,773
(SIGHING)

617
00:59:40,149 --> 00:59:41,439
STEINER: Anselm.

618
00:59:44,899 --> 00:59:46,273
Welcome back, Sergeant.

619
00:59:48,565 --> 00:59:50,398
- Hollerbach!
- Rolf, hello.

620
00:59:50,524 --> 00:59:53,564
DIETZ: Good to have you back, Schnurrbart.

621
01:00:00,815 --> 01:00:01,939
Krüger!

622
01:00:10,982 --> 01:00:13,398
You're back too soon.
I don't want to talk to you.

623
01:00:13,482 --> 01:00:14,731
Leave me alone.

624
01:00:14,815 --> 01:00:16,689
Get your ass out of there, you old pirate.

625
01:00:16,774 --> 01:00:18,106
(LAUGHS)

626
01:00:18,399 --> 01:00:21,398
I missed you. I missed you! Yeah.

627
01:00:22,399 --> 01:00:23,814
My, my, my! What is this?

628
01:00:23,899 --> 01:00:26,481
ANSELM: That's Zoll.
HOLLERBACH: That's a Party member Zoll.

629
01:00:26,565 --> 01:00:28,689
KERN: With compliments of Captain Stransky.

630
01:00:28,774 --> 01:00:30,648
S. S. Special Action Squad.

631
01:00:30,732 --> 01:00:32,064
STEINER: You still a Party member,
Hollerbach?

632
01:00:32,149 --> 01:00:35,064
Well, Rolf, I'd dance with the party
if I could find one.

633
01:00:35,232 --> 01:00:36,356
(LAUGHS)

634
01:00:36,482 --> 01:00:40,564
Hey, silence. The Party's convinced
we are winning the war.

635
01:00:41,190 --> 01:00:43,398
Yeah, sure, we're winning the war.

636
01:00:43,815 --> 01:00:45,148
(MEN LAUGHING)

637
01:00:46,815 --> 01:00:51,439
I hope you've memorised our serial numbers,

638
01:00:51,524 --> 01:00:55,398
our mothers' maiden names correctly.

639
01:00:58,357 --> 01:01:02,064
I wouldn't want the Gestapo to come and
arrest the wrong man, woman or child.

640
01:01:03,399 --> 01:01:07,648
I don't care what you believe,
or what you've done.

641
01:01:09,399 --> 01:01:12,856
Your duty is to us, the platoon and me.

642
01:01:14,024 --> 01:01:19,106
Fulfil those responsibilities or you will have
a bayonet up your ass.

643
01:01:20,065 --> 01:01:21,898
- Clear?
- Yes, sir.

644
01:01:22,315 --> 01:01:25,439
KRÜGER: I am playing nursemaid
to the third squad, any volunteers?

645
01:01:25,524 --> 01:01:27,314
(BLOWS RASPBERRY)

646
01:01:27,399 --> 01:01:28,981
- Not me.
- SOLDIER 1 : No chance.

647
01:01:29,065 --> 01:01:32,106
SOLDIER 2: Go alone this time.
SOLDIER 3: Enjoy yourself.

648
01:01:32,232 --> 01:01:33,439
KRÜGER: Thanks a lot.

649
01:01:33,565 --> 01:01:36,064
What have we here, a hawk and a hare, eh?
I'll take you.

650
01:01:38,315 --> 01:01:39,606
Come on, have a drink.

651
01:01:39,690 --> 01:01:41,981
- That's your bottle.
- Cheers, Rolf.

652
01:01:42,065 --> 01:01:45,023
Ah, give me that thing. Come on.

653
01:01:46,440 --> 01:01:47,731
Gentlemen.

654
01:01:48,149 --> 01:01:49,148
SOLDIER 4: Cheers.

655
01:01:50,357 --> 01:01:52,439
TRIEBIG: Some papers
for you to sign, Captain.

656
01:01:52,524 --> 01:01:54,981
- STRANSKY: I'll sign them later.
- (RAT SQUEALING)

657
01:01:55,065 --> 01:01:58,856
Stop that! Be careful with my J. J.

658
01:01:59,315 --> 01:02:00,606
Yes, sir.

659
01:02:01,065 --> 01:02:03,189
Have her treated correctly.

660
01:02:03,982 --> 01:02:07,398
- Sergeant Steiner reporting as ordered, sir.
- Come in.

661
01:02:11,190 --> 01:02:13,814
Thank you. That will be all, gentlemen.

662
01:02:17,440 --> 01:02:20,231
- Welcome back, Sergeant Steiner.
- Thank you, sir.

663
01:02:21,107 --> 01:02:24,898
Please sit down. Make yourself comfortable.

664
01:02:25,982 --> 01:02:27,731
(FAINT INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC ON RADIO)

665
01:02:32,107 --> 01:02:35,231
Well, now that you're back,
and I'm glad you're back.

666
01:02:36,274 --> 01:02:40,189
I think we should make a fresh start together.

667
01:02:40,899 --> 01:02:44,148
But the main point is

668
01:02:45,524 --> 01:02:50,148
the regiment feels or believes

669
01:02:52,190 --> 01:02:54,064
that I deserve the Iron Cross now.

670
01:02:54,982 --> 01:02:58,356
And they've asked me to produce
two witnesses to the fact

671
01:02:58,690 --> 01:03:02,523
that I led the counterattack and threw
the Russians out of their positions.

672
01:03:02,774 --> 01:03:07,398
I have named Lieutenant Triebig and you.

673
01:03:08,649 --> 01:03:10,064
Especially you.

674
01:03:12,065 --> 01:03:15,856
Lieutenant Triebig
has already submitted his signature.

675
01:03:27,607 --> 01:03:31,648
Am I to believe this is a private conversation?

676
01:03:33,940 --> 01:03:36,398
That would occur to you, wouldn't it?

677
01:03:36,774 --> 01:03:41,231
All right, have some wine, a '36 Mosel.

678
01:03:44,149 --> 01:03:45,773
I'll have some.

679
01:03:51,982 --> 01:03:53,939
Thank you, Sergeant.

680
01:03:57,815 --> 01:04:04,564
But still remember that in civilian
as well as in military life

681
01:04:04,732 --> 01:04:06,898
the distinction is made between people.

682
01:04:09,482 --> 01:04:13,731
Is that what you meant when you said,
"All you are and may become

683
01:04:15,024 --> 01:04:18,023
"is dependent upon this present company?"

684
01:04:19,857 --> 01:04:22,731
Well, the difference

685
01:04:24,607 --> 01:04:27,648
is a matter of ethical

686
01:04:30,232 --> 01:04:34,814
and intellectual superiority which is caused,

687
01:04:34,899 --> 01:04:39,523
whether you like it or not,
by blood and by class difference.

688
01:04:40,315 --> 01:04:45,023
If I remember correctly Kant was
the son of a saddle maker

689
01:04:45,107 --> 01:04:48,689
and Schubert's father
was a poor schoolmaster.

690
01:04:50,399 --> 01:04:55,606
Perhaps talent, sensitivity and character
are no longer privileges

691
01:04:55,690 --> 01:04:59,481
of the so-called upper class.

692
01:04:59,565 --> 01:05:02,731
But Kant and Schubert were exceptions.

693
01:05:03,232 --> 01:05:06,064
We're talking about general concepts,

694
01:05:07,857 --> 01:05:12,689
- not individuals.
- But I am one and so are you.

695
01:05:13,899 --> 01:05:17,564
Didn't your führersay that
all class distinctions were to be abolished?

696
01:05:18,107 --> 01:05:22,023
I'm an officer of the Wehrmacht.
I've never been a Party member.

697
01:05:22,149 --> 01:05:23,939
I'm a Prussian aristocrat

698
01:05:24,024 --> 01:05:26,648
and I don't want to be put
into the same category!

699
01:05:26,732 --> 01:05:28,231
So we agree for once.

700
01:05:29,524 --> 01:05:30,731
Good.

701
01:05:33,607 --> 01:05:35,273
But he is still our führer.

702
01:05:37,899 --> 01:05:39,481
Unfortunately.

703
01:05:39,982 --> 01:05:41,231
Oh...

704
01:05:42,857 --> 01:05:44,273
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

705
01:05:44,399 --> 01:05:48,064
That is a different question, Sergeant.

706
01:05:48,565 --> 01:05:50,273
That's not up to us to judge.

707
01:05:50,815 --> 01:05:52,731
Why do you want it so badly?

708
01:05:57,857 --> 01:06:00,523
It's just a piece of worthless metal.

709
01:06:02,274 --> 01:06:03,398
Look!

710
01:06:06,815 --> 01:06:08,648
It's not worthless to me.

711
01:06:09,149 --> 01:06:10,981
Why is it so important to you?

712
01:06:12,440 --> 01:06:14,023
Tell me, Captain, why?

713
01:06:18,190 --> 01:06:20,731
Sergeant, if I go back

714
01:06:24,065 --> 01:06:26,064
without the Iron Cross

715
01:06:29,899 --> 01:06:31,939
I couldn't face my family.

716
01:06:36,940 --> 01:06:38,106
(BOMB EXPLODING)

717
01:06:38,399 --> 01:06:41,898
Personally, sir, I don't feel
you deserve the Iron Cross.

718
01:06:55,357 --> 01:06:56,814
Incoming!

719
01:07:16,190 --> 01:07:17,231
Where are you going?

720
01:07:17,482 --> 01:07:19,981
I'm going to point 1 24.
Corporal Krüger's over there.

721
01:07:20,065 --> 01:07:22,523
Are you crazy?
No one could survive this kind of assault.

722
01:07:22,607 --> 01:07:25,064
Get out of my way, God damn it.
I'm going after him.

723
01:07:28,315 --> 01:07:29,564
Steiner!

724
01:07:29,649 --> 01:07:31,689
You get me some stretcher-bearers, damn it.

725
01:07:32,524 --> 01:07:34,231
Steiner! Steiner!

726
01:07:46,857 --> 01:07:48,106
(SCREAMING)

727
01:09:08,399 --> 01:09:09,814
The others?

728
01:09:12,690 --> 01:09:14,231
Dead, all dead.

729
01:09:27,732 --> 01:09:29,856
Oh, God. Listen to me.

730
01:09:36,732 --> 01:09:38,773
We are going to leave now.

731
01:09:40,232 --> 01:09:43,064
Will you get up and follow me out of here?

732
01:09:44,190 --> 01:09:45,481
All right?

733
01:09:49,024 --> 01:09:50,398
Three hours.

734
01:09:53,107 --> 01:09:56,814
Three hours I've been here by myself.

735
01:10:01,065 --> 01:10:02,231
(EXHALES)

736
01:10:02,440 --> 01:10:10,314
I don't ever want to be alone again.

737
01:10:10,399 --> 01:10:12,231
You won't, you won't.

738
01:10:12,440 --> 01:10:13,856
(BOMB EXPLODES)

739
01:10:16,399 --> 01:10:18,064
(MACHINE GUN FIRING)

740
01:10:23,274 --> 01:10:24,523
Come on.

741
01:10:26,190 --> 01:10:29,231
Why the hell wasn't I told
of Steiner's return to the battalion?

742
01:10:29,357 --> 01:10:33,023
My apologies for that, sir.
There were more important things to do.

743
01:10:33,565 --> 01:10:34,856
I want him here at once.

744
01:10:35,315 --> 01:10:37,356
... about a predicament of which I am sure

745
01:10:37,440 --> 01:10:38,773
you don't need to be reminded.

746
01:10:39,232 --> 01:10:41,648
- Clear, Stransky?
- Quite clear, sir.

747
01:10:44,357 --> 01:10:45,689
Now we shall see.

748
01:10:46,149 --> 01:10:48,398
I don't like the tone of his voice.

749
01:10:49,149 --> 01:10:51,189
I'm fed up with the whole situation.

750
01:10:51,274 --> 01:10:53,189
Well, it doesn't matter any more.

751
01:10:53,899 --> 01:10:57,356
I know from reliable sources
that headquarters

752
01:10:57,440 --> 01:11:01,689
have already written off
the Kuban bridgehead.

753
01:11:03,482 --> 01:11:06,564
And soon the whole Crimea
will be a cul-de-sac.

754
01:11:08,482 --> 01:11:10,564
Report to Brandt.

755
01:11:13,149 --> 01:11:17,148
If you have the choice, Triebig,
between Biarritz and Siberia,

756
01:11:18,649 --> 01:11:20,064
what would you choose?

757
01:11:23,857 --> 01:11:25,856
- Steiner.
- Colonel.

758
01:11:28,857 --> 01:11:30,231
Sit down please, Steiner.

759
01:11:36,524 --> 01:11:37,648
How was hospital?

760
01:11:37,732 --> 01:11:40,898
Oh, interesting.

761
01:11:42,399 --> 01:11:43,814
I recommend it.

762
01:11:51,190 --> 01:11:56,856
Did Captain Stransky lead the counterattack

763
01:11:57,232 --> 01:11:59,398
the day Lieutenant Meyer was killed?

764
01:12:04,274 --> 01:12:06,023
Lieutenant Meyer led the attack.

765
01:12:06,107 --> 01:12:08,731
Captain Stransky was nowhere in sight.

766
01:12:09,565 --> 01:12:11,064
You're sure of that.

767
01:12:13,649 --> 01:12:15,398
I saw Lieutenant Meyer die.

768
01:12:15,482 --> 01:12:17,106
(BOMB EXPLODING)

769
01:12:19,315 --> 01:12:20,398
Fetch Triebig.

770
01:12:21,732 --> 01:12:23,689
Stay, I want you to listen.

771
01:12:28,649 --> 01:12:29,856
Sir?

772
01:12:33,815 --> 01:12:35,648
You signed your Captain's report.

773
01:12:35,732 --> 01:12:38,523
Were you present when Captain Stransky
led the counterattack?

774
01:12:40,940 --> 01:12:43,939
I accompanied Captain Stransky to the field

775
01:12:45,357 --> 01:12:48,064
and saw him calling several men around him.

776
01:12:48,482 --> 01:12:51,189
Then he sent me back to the command post.

777
01:12:51,774 --> 01:12:55,064
Then how do you know that Captain Stransky
led the counterattack?

778
01:12:55,232 --> 01:12:58,148
You've signed a statement
to that effect, Triebig.

779
01:12:58,399 --> 01:13:03,064
I wasn't there. I learned of it from
wounded men who were returning.

780
01:13:03,649 --> 01:13:06,439
Can you give me the name of
one of these wounded men?

781
01:13:06,774 --> 01:13:10,773
They were not staff men, just company men.

782
01:13:11,815 --> 01:13:13,481
I knew them only by sight.

783
01:13:13,565 --> 01:13:16,398
Besides, the smoke, the battle.
We had been under fire, sir.

784
01:13:19,107 --> 01:13:23,273
I want you to know, Triebig,
that I have had your statement checked.

785
01:13:25,399 --> 01:13:29,064
Captain Kiesel will inform you
of the results of our investigation.

786
01:13:33,274 --> 01:13:37,148
Our investigation so far has disclosed

787
01:13:38,857 --> 01:13:45,273
that the men in the second company who
took part in the action declared unanimously

788
01:13:46,440 --> 01:13:49,939
that the action was led by Lieutenant Meyer.

789
01:13:53,899 --> 01:13:58,564
None of them saw Captain Stransky
or Lieutenant Triebig.

790
01:14:05,649 --> 01:14:09,273
To my mind there is nothing
more contemptible

791
01:14:09,440 --> 01:14:12,231
than stealing the laurels which
properly belong to a man

792
01:14:12,315 --> 01:14:14,189
who was killed in action.

793
01:14:15,315 --> 01:14:18,314
If Sergeant Steiner stands
by his last testimony,

794
01:14:18,399 --> 01:14:21,689
I should be compelled to
institute disciplinary proceedings

795
01:14:21,774 --> 01:14:26,231
against the Captain and you.

796
01:14:27,065 --> 01:14:28,314
Yes, sir.

797
01:14:29,024 --> 01:14:31,689
Do you stand by your statement
that Captain Stransky

798
01:14:31,774 --> 01:14:33,523
was not with the company?

799
01:14:33,607 --> 01:14:35,148
(BOMB EXPLODING)

800
01:14:51,357 --> 01:14:52,564
(EXHALES)

801
01:14:56,524 --> 01:15:02,564
Would it be possible for me to give
my answer in three or four days, sir?

802
01:15:02,982 --> 01:15:05,106
Did you see Stransky or not?

803
01:15:10,607 --> 01:15:11,898
(EXHALES)

804
01:15:22,065 --> 01:15:25,023
You may go, Triebig.
You're no longer needed.

805
01:15:28,232 --> 01:15:30,564
What in God's name has got into you?
This is your chance!

806
01:15:31,190 --> 01:15:33,439
You are the only person
that stands between Stransky

807
01:15:33,524 --> 01:15:35,064
and his Iron Cross.

808
01:15:35,190 --> 01:15:37,231
And you could be called as
a primary witness against him

809
01:15:37,357 --> 01:15:38,606
in a court of honour.

810
01:15:40,190 --> 01:15:43,148
My differences with Captain Stransky
are a personal matter.

811
01:15:44,024 --> 01:15:45,023
BRANDT: Now listen to me.

812
01:15:45,107 --> 01:15:49,356
You know that I've always shown
a great deal of understanding for you,

813
01:15:49,440 --> 01:15:52,564
but I'm becoming tired of
battling with your superiors.

814
01:15:53,440 --> 01:15:55,231
I never ask you to.

815
01:15:56,690 --> 01:15:58,398
Didn't ask me to!

816
01:16:02,899 --> 01:16:06,023
You never asked me to?
Are you out of your mind?

817
01:16:06,899 --> 01:16:09,231
Steiner, why are you so ungrateful?

818
01:16:14,857 --> 01:16:21,064
What do I have to be grateful for, Captain?

819
01:16:22,107 --> 01:16:23,648
Your tolerance?

820
01:16:24,732 --> 01:16:28,689
Do you think that just because
you and Colonel Brandt

821
01:16:28,774 --> 01:16:32,231
are more enlightened than most officers
that I hate you any less?

822
01:16:37,274 --> 01:16:40,106
I hate all officers,

823
01:16:41,357 --> 01:16:43,648
all the Stranskys, all the Triebigs,

824
01:16:43,732 --> 01:16:46,856
all the Iron Cross scavengers
in the whole German army.

825
01:16:49,274 --> 01:16:51,606
Have you any idea what you're saying?

826
01:16:57,774 --> 01:17:02,273
Do you know how much I hate this uniform

827
01:17:03,732 --> 01:17:05,939
and everything it stands for?

828
01:17:07,024 --> 01:17:08,064
God!

829
01:17:11,690 --> 01:17:12,898
Get out.

830
01:17:15,190 --> 01:17:16,939
Please, just get out.

831
01:17:17,440 --> 01:17:18,814
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

832
01:17:19,232 --> 01:17:21,231
ORDERLY: Regimental headquarters.

833
01:17:23,399 --> 01:17:24,523
Division headquarters, sir.

834
01:17:24,982 --> 01:17:27,106
General Von Kellinshofe.

835
01:17:28,732 --> 01:17:30,231
Colonel Brandt.

836
01:17:31,399 --> 01:17:32,856
Yes, General.

837
01:17:37,940 --> 01:17:41,023
Yes, sir. I didn't know it was as bad as that.

838
01:17:41,357 --> 01:17:43,398
I am very sorry to hear it.

839
01:17:48,690 --> 01:17:49,773
Well?

840
01:17:49,857 --> 01:17:52,064
We're pulling back
to the bridgehead at Kuban.

841
01:17:54,149 --> 01:17:56,981
No rear guard. Not even Steiner's platoon.

842
01:17:58,107 --> 01:18:00,648
We're not retreating. We're running.

843
01:18:00,857 --> 01:18:02,481
(BOMB EXPLODING)

844
01:18:14,607 --> 01:18:17,981
Captain Stransky. Yes, Captain Kiesel.

845
01:18:18,065 --> 01:18:20,189
I was just about to leave.

846
01:18:20,357 --> 01:18:23,064
Don't leave just yet. Now listen to me.

847
01:18:25,774 --> 01:18:30,273
Regiment feels that it is unwise
and also suicidal

848
01:18:30,357 --> 01:18:34,481
to leave behind any rear guard
platoons including Steiner's.

849
01:18:35,732 --> 01:18:38,064
I want them to join the
evacuation immediately.

850
01:18:39,024 --> 01:18:40,773
You understand that?

851
01:18:41,065 --> 01:18:42,148
Yes, Captain.

852
01:18:44,149 --> 01:18:45,398
Triebig?

853
01:18:47,899 --> 01:18:51,606
All real guard platoons
to join the evacuation immediately.

854
01:18:51,690 --> 01:18:53,981
Shall I notify Steiner's platoon?

855
01:18:56,565 --> 01:18:57,606
Yes.

856
01:19:02,899 --> 01:19:04,481
Give me Steiner.

857
01:19:34,690 --> 01:19:36,356
Calling Regiment.

858
01:19:39,024 --> 01:19:40,481
Regimental headquarters. Come in, please!

859
01:19:40,565 --> 01:19:42,564
Regimental headquarters! Come in, please!

860
01:19:45,190 --> 01:19:47,523
Regimental headquarters. Come in, please!

861
01:19:57,399 --> 01:19:58,898
B Company, can you hear me?

862
01:19:58,982 --> 01:20:00,731
Anybody come in, please!

863
01:20:05,899 --> 01:20:07,064
Tanks!

864
01:20:16,274 --> 01:20:17,523
ANSELM: Captain Stransky,
can you hear me?

865
01:20:17,607 --> 01:20:18,981
Krüger!

866
01:20:21,024 --> 01:20:22,564
All the lines are out.

867
01:20:51,399 --> 01:20:53,564
STEINER: Better get 'em out!
Down the tunnel!

868
01:20:54,732 --> 01:20:55,773
Out!

869
01:20:57,107 --> 01:20:58,606
Go into the factory.

870
01:20:59,982 --> 01:21:01,273
Get everything?

871
01:21:03,815 --> 01:21:04,856
Fire!

872
01:21:29,899 --> 01:21:32,064
- (SOLDIERS SHOUTING)
- (MACHINE GUN FIRE)

873
01:23:10,107 --> 01:23:12,189
Zoll, grab some mines. Bring them up. Quick!

874
01:23:18,982 --> 01:23:21,398
STEINER: On the tracks, Zoll.
Put them on the tracks.

875
01:23:21,649 --> 01:23:23,356
(ENGINE STRUGGLING)

876
01:23:23,482 --> 01:23:24,898
Hurry! Move!

877
01:23:31,440 --> 01:23:32,814
STEINER: Heads down.

878
01:23:44,065 --> 01:23:47,356
Into the factory. Over to the factory!
Move, damn it!

879
01:23:59,149 --> 01:24:00,731
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING)

880
01:24:10,565 --> 01:24:11,731
(EXCLAIMS)

881
01:24:25,732 --> 01:24:27,564
Maag, they're coming in from both sides.

882
01:24:27,649 --> 01:24:31,273
Kern, up above!
Krüger, get up on the gangwalk! Hurry.

883
01:24:47,565 --> 01:24:49,106
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

884
01:25:10,024 --> 01:25:11,523
Quick! Down the tunnel!

885
01:25:41,524 --> 01:25:45,648
Anselm! The grenade! Come here!

886
01:25:50,399 --> 01:25:51,814
Throw it!

887
01:25:53,065 --> 01:25:55,356
Shit! Jesus Christ!

888
01:26:42,024 --> 01:26:43,689
Steiner, let's go!

889
01:26:54,607 --> 01:26:55,648
STEINER: It's clear.

890
01:27:00,774 --> 01:27:02,564
Dietz. Cover for us.

891
01:27:23,899 --> 01:27:25,273
SOLDIER: Hurry! Move!

892
01:27:41,024 --> 01:27:43,314
- Captain Pucher reporting, sir.
- Ah, yes, Captain.

893
01:27:43,399 --> 01:27:44,814
You have your orders?

894
01:27:44,899 --> 01:27:47,564
PUCHER: And a letter for you
to be delivered personally.

895
01:27:47,649 --> 01:27:48,898
Thank you.

896
01:27:52,940 --> 01:27:54,856
You can guess what this is, can't you?

897
01:27:56,857 --> 01:27:59,523
- A transfer.
- Exactly.

898
01:28:00,440 --> 01:28:04,231
Our Stransky is to report
to Paris within a week.

899
01:28:05,274 --> 01:28:08,648
Captain Pucher,
my orderly will see to your billeting.

900
01:28:08,732 --> 01:28:12,356
But don't unpack everything.
We might be going away.

901
01:28:12,982 --> 01:28:14,023
Captain.

902
01:28:16,899 --> 01:28:19,939
(EXHALES) Stransky.

903
01:28:20,024 --> 01:28:22,106
Without Steiner to contradict him,

904
01:28:22,190 --> 01:28:24,814
he'll get his Iron Cross
and strut all around Paris.

905
01:28:24,899 --> 01:28:28,398
The arrogant, unbloodied bastard.

906
01:28:29,732 --> 01:28:32,314
Stransky in Paris and Steiner...

907
01:28:33,482 --> 01:28:35,523
God knows where he'll be.

908
01:28:35,774 --> 01:28:37,606
It seems there's...

909
01:28:37,690 --> 01:28:40,856
What, 22, 23 kilometres between...

910
01:28:42,357 --> 01:28:44,023
... here and Anapa.

911
01:28:45,899 --> 01:28:48,439
Marshland. Wilderness.

912
01:28:49,565 --> 01:28:51,648
It's the same trap behind the Russian lines.

913
01:28:51,732 --> 01:28:53,648
Again shit, again shit, again shit...

914
01:28:53,732 --> 01:28:57,314
Here take your gun.
Again shit, again shit, again shit...

915
01:28:57,399 --> 01:28:58,856
We'll try the road.

916
01:28:58,940 --> 01:29:02,148
(RUSSIAN SOLDIERS SINGING)

917
01:29:35,649 --> 01:29:38,189
(STAMMERING) Hey, we'll never
get over this road.

918
01:29:38,274 --> 01:29:39,273
Shh!

919
01:29:39,899 --> 01:29:41,189
What's your hurry, kid?

920
01:29:41,274 --> 01:29:43,523
We'll get out of this mess
in time for the next one.

921
01:30:02,774 --> 01:30:05,439
Steiner! Steiner, it's clear now.

922
01:30:12,190 --> 01:30:15,564
(WHISPERING) Let's go. Move it, move it!

923
01:30:17,607 --> 01:30:19,939
Anselm, move your ass!

924
01:30:32,315 --> 01:30:34,731
BRANDT: The cattle cars
or whatever they're sending

925
01:30:34,815 --> 01:30:37,398
are due to arrive at 1 200 hours,

926
01:30:37,482 --> 01:30:41,981
provided, of course, that the Russian sappers
have not blown up the track.

927
01:30:42,274 --> 01:30:44,231
- Any questions?
- No, sir.

928
01:30:46,899 --> 01:30:48,231
Dismissed.

929
01:30:52,732 --> 01:30:57,064
Carry on probing and aggressive actions
all along the front.

930
01:31:00,107 --> 01:31:01,231
(DOOR SLAMS)

931
01:31:02,232 --> 01:31:04,064
They're not listening.

932
01:31:09,565 --> 01:31:10,856
You, too.

933
01:31:13,440 --> 01:31:14,523
I beg your pardon?

934
01:31:16,649 --> 01:31:18,064
(SIGHS)

935
01:31:19,482 --> 01:31:20,939
BRANDT: Who needs a railroad track?

936
01:31:21,024 --> 01:31:27,523
When we break out of here, we'll push on
with a blitzkrieg through Stalingrad

937
01:31:29,065 --> 01:31:31,481
and up to the outskirts of Moscow.

938
01:31:39,232 --> 01:31:42,314
What will we do when we lose the war?

939
01:31:46,357 --> 01:31:48,398
Prepare for the next one.

940
01:32:07,815 --> 01:32:09,773
Do you think he'll get through?

941
01:32:11,899 --> 01:32:13,148
Steiner?

942
01:32:15,274 --> 01:32:16,814
I don't see how he can.

943
01:32:26,399 --> 01:32:28,398
Anselm, go bring Zoll in.

944
01:32:34,232 --> 01:32:36,064
- What is it?
- Bridge.

945
01:32:36,149 --> 01:32:38,356
Just bring what you need to kill with.

946
01:32:53,815 --> 01:32:55,314
- It's a game.
- A game?

947
01:32:57,982 --> 01:33:00,606
It's a kid's game.
It's bad luck to step on sunlight.

948
01:33:02,940 --> 01:33:06,356
I thought perhaps if I miss the beams

949
01:33:06,440 --> 01:33:09,564
we would all come through this all right.

950
01:33:12,982 --> 01:33:13,981
Come on.

951
01:34:08,149 --> 01:34:10,023
(SOLDIERS CONVERSING IN RUSSIAN)

952
01:35:49,024 --> 01:35:50,023
(GRUNTS)

953
01:36:07,190 --> 01:36:08,564
(WOMEN CONVERSING IN RUSSIAN)

954
01:36:23,399 --> 01:36:24,939
(FLIES BUZZING)

955
01:36:31,732 --> 01:36:33,273
(CRYING)

956
01:36:43,524 --> 01:36:45,564
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

957
01:36:58,940 --> 01:37:00,356
(HENS CLUCKING)

958
01:37:27,774 --> 01:37:29,856
DIETZ: Come on, come on.
Over there, get in the corner.

959
01:37:30,149 --> 01:37:31,606
Jesus Christ!

960
01:37:36,065 --> 01:37:37,814
Get these weapons out of here!

961
01:37:37,899 --> 01:37:40,398
Krüger, upstairs! Schnurrbart, perimeter.

962
01:37:41,607 --> 01:37:42,939
Check the other buildings.

963
01:37:45,649 --> 01:37:48,856
Come here. Get in that corner.
Get in that room.

964
01:37:49,565 --> 01:37:51,356
Come on, pretty rabbit.

965
01:37:51,440 --> 01:37:54,606
(LAUGHS) Don't hide from me.

966
01:37:55,357 --> 01:37:58,064
STEINER: Check the radio,
and get that body out of here.

967
01:37:58,899 --> 01:38:00,189
Anselm.

968
01:38:00,274 --> 01:38:03,106
- Stay there!
- SOLDIER: Get your hands off.

969
01:38:06,482 --> 01:38:08,148
STEINER: Anselm, stop it, damn it!

970
01:38:08,565 --> 01:38:10,648
- (LAUGHS MANIACALLY)
- (WOMAN PROTESTING)

971
01:38:10,732 --> 01:38:13,481
- Anselm! Anselm!
- Leave me, Steiner.

972
01:38:13,565 --> 01:38:15,231
Wait. Stop it!

973
01:38:16,774 --> 01:38:21,106
Stop your fucking silly game!
This isn't a brothel!

974
01:38:21,899 --> 01:38:23,648
This is a war!

975
01:38:25,399 --> 01:38:29,231
Rolf, look what I found. (LAUGHS)

976
01:38:30,899 --> 01:38:32,564
STEINER: I said get that body out of here.

977
01:38:35,232 --> 01:38:36,981
SCHNURRBART: Everything clear out here.

978
01:38:38,190 --> 01:38:39,648
What is this?

979
01:38:42,565 --> 01:38:45,523
It shows their basic positions
in front of Anapa.

980
01:38:45,815 --> 01:38:47,356
- (CHUCKLES)
- STEINER: Good.

981
01:38:47,732 --> 01:38:48,939
Means we're halfway home.

982
01:38:50,607 --> 01:38:52,231
Thank the ladies

983
01:38:53,024 --> 01:38:55,523
and tell them to take their clothes off.

984
01:38:55,607 --> 01:38:59,398
And what shall we do with the bodies?
Who's gonna keep them warm?

985
01:38:59,482 --> 01:39:02,148
- Tell them we want their tunics and trousers.
- We are going to die anyway.

986
01:39:02,232 --> 01:39:03,814
- Do it! Do it!
- We are going to die anyway. Let me...

987
01:39:03,899 --> 01:39:05,189
Let me keep one.

988
01:39:09,690 --> 01:39:12,023
(KRÜGER INSTRUCTING WOMEN IN RUSSIAN)

989
01:39:24,690 --> 01:39:26,106
(WOMEN GASP)

990
01:39:26,482 --> 01:39:28,064
(KRÜGER CONTINUES IN RUSSIAN)

991
01:39:32,899 --> 01:39:35,148
(WHISPERING IN RUSSIAN)

992
01:39:35,815 --> 01:39:37,439
Major.

993
01:39:38,732 --> 01:39:39,898
Major!

994
01:39:44,232 --> 01:39:45,564
She's dead.

995
01:39:48,857 --> 01:39:51,564
- Dietz, Zoll, watch them.
- Yeah.

996
01:39:52,899 --> 01:39:54,898
The rest of you, put these uniforms on.

997
01:39:54,982 --> 01:39:56,689
(SHOUTING IN RUSSIAN)

998
01:39:59,065 --> 01:40:00,648
Come on, get over there with the rest of them.

999
01:40:13,940 --> 01:40:15,731
Pick up your weapons.

1000
01:40:16,232 --> 01:40:17,981
Up, up, out!

1001
01:40:22,232 --> 01:40:24,023
(SHOUTING IN RUSSIAN)

1002
01:40:24,565 --> 01:40:26,273
Get that uniform and take it inside.

1003
01:40:26,357 --> 01:40:28,564
(CONVERSING IN RUSSIAN)

1004
01:40:36,232 --> 01:40:37,564
Oh, shit.

1005
01:40:55,565 --> 01:40:57,773
(GERMAN SOLDIERS CONVERSING OUTSIDE)

1006
01:41:04,857 --> 01:41:07,606
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

1007
01:41:08,565 --> 01:41:09,898
Ah, go over there.

1008
01:41:12,565 --> 01:41:14,064
- (GRUNTS IN PAIN)
- Come on, pick it up.

1009
01:41:14,149 --> 01:41:16,898
- (LAUGHS)
- You want to play? All right.

1010
01:41:16,982 --> 01:41:18,523
That's a nice little girl.

1011
01:41:19,190 --> 01:41:20,898
That's it.

1012
01:41:21,190 --> 01:41:24,606
Come on. (LAUGHING)
I'll give you something to play with.

1013
01:41:26,565 --> 01:41:29,106
- I'm gonna be busy for a while.
- (CHUCKLES)

1014
01:41:30,232 --> 01:41:32,564
- (GRUNTS)
- Come on.

1015
01:41:36,940 --> 01:41:38,356
(CHICKENS CLUCKING)

1016
01:41:45,065 --> 01:41:46,773
How would you like it, huh?

1017
01:41:53,565 --> 01:41:54,981
That's nice.

1018
01:42:05,440 --> 01:42:06,731
Ah.

1019
01:42:06,815 --> 01:42:36,898
(GRUNTS)

1020
01:42:43,232 --> 01:42:44,398
(GASPS)

1021
01:42:45,899 --> 01:42:47,398
(BOTH SOBBING SOFTLY)

1022
01:42:51,940 --> 01:42:53,564
(MOANING)

1023
01:42:57,774 --> 01:42:59,148
DIETZ: Steiner!

1024
01:43:02,190 --> 01:43:03,939
Oh, Dietz.

1025
01:43:04,857 --> 01:43:06,731
Jesus Christ.

1026
01:43:08,190 --> 01:43:09,231
Dietz.

1027
01:43:10,232 --> 01:43:12,273
Oh, God. God.

1028
01:43:14,649 --> 01:43:16,023
Don't...

1029
01:43:17,607 --> 01:43:19,273
... hurt the girl.

1030
01:43:25,982 --> 01:43:27,064
(MOANS)

1031
01:43:27,357 --> 01:43:29,481
ANSELM: Do you believe in God, Sergeant?

1032
01:43:29,565 --> 01:43:33,398
I believe God is a sadist

1033
01:43:36,857 --> 01:43:39,523
but probably doesn't even know it.

1034
01:43:41,065 --> 01:43:43,023
(SCREAMING)

1035
01:43:46,482 --> 01:43:47,606
Zoll!

1036
01:43:48,565 --> 01:43:50,231
(ZOLL CRYING OUT)

1037
01:44:00,232 --> 01:44:01,564
Stupid man!

1038
01:44:06,232 --> 01:44:08,898
Steiner! God!

1039
01:44:10,732 --> 01:44:13,731
Take the women outside. With me.

1040
01:44:14,482 --> 01:44:17,481
Come on. Go!

1041
01:44:17,565 --> 01:44:19,856
Move out! Come on!

1042
01:44:23,065 --> 01:44:25,273
All of you get inside. Inside!

1043
01:44:29,149 --> 01:44:30,648
(CRYING) Steiner!

1044
01:44:31,899 --> 01:44:32,939
(ZOLL SCREAMS)

1045
01:44:34,232 --> 01:44:35,731
Now we're even.

1046
01:44:48,399 --> 01:44:50,189
(SHOUTING IN RUSSIAN)

1047
01:44:50,274 --> 01:44:51,856
(WOMEN GRUNTING)

1048
01:44:52,690 --> 01:44:54,231
(ZOLL CRYING)

1049
01:44:57,315 --> 01:44:59,689
BRANDT: And there's one other thing
you could do for me.

1050
01:44:59,774 --> 01:45:04,148
There's a man here
that I would like to get out quickly.

1051
01:45:04,899 --> 01:45:07,356
I spoke to you about him before.

1052
01:45:07,440 --> 01:45:11,773
If there is a chance that he could leave
with your headquarter staff,

1053
01:45:11,982 --> 01:45:14,856
I will be most grateful. Thank you, sir.

1054
01:45:15,065 --> 01:45:17,606
KIESEL: They're rolling up both flanks.

1055
01:45:18,190 --> 01:45:19,398
It's chaos.

1056
01:45:19,899 --> 01:45:22,189
That need no longer concern you.

1057
01:45:22,274 --> 01:45:23,898
(SHELLS EXPLODING)

1058
01:45:23,982 --> 01:45:26,398
You're to report at once
to General Headquarters.

1059
01:45:26,482 --> 01:45:28,398
You're being evacuated.

1060
01:45:31,482 --> 01:45:33,731
I can't leave the Command, sir.

1061
01:45:34,024 --> 01:45:39,356
While I'm still in a condition to issue orders,
those orders will be obeyed.

1062
01:45:41,315 --> 01:45:43,398
I'm prepared to disobey that order, sir.

1063
01:45:47,982 --> 01:45:49,898
You've been around Steiner too long.

1064
01:45:50,732 --> 01:45:53,064
Come, listen to me for a moment.

1065
01:45:58,149 --> 01:46:03,273
For many of us Germans,
the exterminator is long overdue.

1066
01:46:03,732 --> 01:46:07,231
But I have decided that you are worth saving.

1067
01:46:08,232 --> 01:46:09,231
(SOLDIER SCREAMS)

1068
01:46:12,274 --> 01:46:14,273
But I'm part of all this.

1069
01:46:15,982 --> 01:46:17,731
There are better people than me.

1070
01:46:19,732 --> 01:46:21,814
Most of them are being killed out there.

1071
01:46:21,899 --> 01:46:25,189
There's nothing wrong with you
except that you smoke too much.

1072
01:46:26,190 --> 01:46:28,731
You're a brave man.
Braver than you think you are.

1073
01:46:29,857 --> 01:46:33,148
One of these days there will be
a need for brave civilians.

1074
01:46:33,232 --> 01:46:34,981
Had you thought of that?

1075
01:46:35,065 --> 01:46:38,606
In the new Germany,
if such a thing is allowed to exist,

1076
01:46:39,690 --> 01:46:41,731
there will be a need
for builders, for thinkers...

1077
01:46:41,815 --> 01:46:43,148
(MACHINE GUN FIRING)

1078
01:46:43,232 --> 01:46:45,023
- BRANDT: For poets.
- (SOLDIERS SCREAMING)

1079
01:46:45,399 --> 01:46:48,523
I begin to see now what your job is to be.

1080
01:46:49,607 --> 01:46:52,106
I will make this my final order to you.

1081
01:46:54,065 --> 01:46:57,606
You will search out
and contact all of these, um...

1082
01:47:00,065 --> 01:47:01,814
... better people, you call them?

1083
01:47:04,524 --> 01:47:09,314
And together you'll take on the responsibility
that goes with survival.

1084
01:47:13,357 --> 01:47:14,898
Now you must leave.

1085
01:47:17,274 --> 01:47:18,731
Please leave.

1086
01:47:24,024 --> 01:47:27,731
Braun, take Captain Kiesel to the railhead!

1087
01:47:35,857 --> 01:47:36,898
Go.

1088
01:47:50,065 --> 01:47:53,898
KRÜGER: Steiner, how do we get
through the Russian trenches?

1089
01:47:57,565 --> 01:47:59,314
It's only a matter of time.

1090
01:48:01,232 --> 01:48:03,439
They'll be building them
for a thousand years.

1091
01:48:04,399 --> 01:48:07,564
- If not here, somewhere else.
- (LAUGHS) Not Germany.

1092
01:48:07,690 --> 01:48:08,939
(LAUGHS)

1093
01:48:09,732 --> 01:48:11,398
(SIGHS) Germany.

1094
01:48:14,899 --> 01:48:17,648
Do you think they'll ever forgive us
for what we've done?

1095
01:48:18,982 --> 01:48:20,439
Or forget us?

1096
01:48:25,899 --> 01:48:30,189
We'll make it. We will make it with your help.

1097
01:48:33,065 --> 01:48:34,814
To tell you the truth I'm...

1098
01:48:36,357 --> 01:48:38,064
I'm beginning to enjoy it.

1099
01:48:39,940 --> 01:48:41,564
Well, you want, uh...

1100
01:48:42,649 --> 01:48:45,148
to be sitting in some mud hole some place,

1101
01:48:45,232 --> 01:48:47,648
waiting for the top of your head
to be blown off?

1102
01:48:49,524 --> 01:48:51,148
At least here we're free.

1103
01:48:51,232 --> 01:48:52,773
(BLOWS INTO HARMONICA)

1104
01:48:52,857 --> 01:48:53,856
MAAG: Steiner.

1105
01:48:55,649 --> 01:48:56,648
Steiner?

1106
01:49:04,940 --> 01:49:06,564
(MAAG PLAYING HARMONICA)

1107
01:49:08,565 --> 01:49:10,356
(ALL SINGING
IM FELDQUARTIER AUF HARTEM STEIN)

1108
01:49:53,774 --> 01:49:55,106
STEINER: Sing it!

1109
01:49:55,190 --> 01:49:57,523
(ALL CONTINUE SINGING)

1110
01:50:05,815 --> 01:50:09,064
(SOLDIERS CONVERSING IN RUSSIAN)

1111
01:51:08,315 --> 01:51:10,439
Go! Go!

1112
01:51:13,565 --> 01:51:15,231
(SHELLS WHISTLING)

1113
01:51:29,690 --> 01:51:31,106
(SHELLS EXPLODING)

1114
01:51:32,690 --> 01:51:33,939
Here, Sergeant. Here's your weapon.

1115
01:51:34,024 --> 01:51:37,023
SCHNURRBART: Then all we have to do
is hope our own artillery doesn't get us.

1116
01:51:37,107 --> 01:51:38,523
KRÜGER: Or the landmines.

1117
01:51:38,607 --> 01:51:39,939
(LAUGHS)

1118
01:51:40,982 --> 01:51:42,564
Two hundred metres to go.

1119
01:51:42,649 --> 01:51:43,689
Anselm.

1120
01:51:43,774 --> 01:51:45,981
- Yes?
- Try to raise somebody on that radio.

1121
01:51:48,399 --> 01:51:50,189
Tell them we're coming in at dawn.

1122
01:51:52,190 --> 01:51:54,189
We need a password. What's, uh...

1123
01:51:55,107 --> 01:51:56,898
What's the password? Uh...

1124
01:51:58,065 --> 01:52:02,106
Reconnaissance Patrol
with several Russian prisoners

1125
01:52:03,399 --> 01:52:04,981
and no shooting.

1126
01:52:06,399 --> 01:52:08,064
Password, Krüger, God damn it!

1127
01:52:10,774 --> 01:52:12,148
"Demarcation. "

1128
01:52:14,899 --> 01:52:18,606
Why not? "Demarcation. "

1129
01:52:20,107 --> 01:52:21,939
"Demarcation. " Sign it Steiner.

1130
01:52:34,107 --> 01:52:37,731
Captain, special password "Demarcation. "
Signed Steiner.

1131
01:52:38,357 --> 01:52:40,356
Coming in with prisoners.

1132
01:52:42,482 --> 01:52:43,939
Looks like a trap.

1133
01:52:44,024 --> 01:52:45,648
My thoughts exactly, sir.

1134
01:52:47,857 --> 01:52:49,856
He may have been captured.

1135
01:52:49,940 --> 01:52:51,564
- Wolf.
- Sir?

1136
01:52:52,232 --> 01:52:53,731
Did you recognise the voice?

1137
01:52:54,565 --> 01:52:56,439
No, sir, it was in code.

1138
01:52:57,565 --> 01:52:59,564
Good code, "Demarcation. "

1139
01:53:00,232 --> 01:53:01,564
Triebig...

1140
01:53:02,149 --> 01:53:04,273
If in the dark,

1141
01:53:06,690 --> 01:53:10,231
you saw half a dozen men,
some in Russian uniforms,

1142
01:53:11,940 --> 01:53:13,564
advancing on you.

1143
01:53:15,315 --> 01:53:17,731
Could anyone blame you if you opened fire?

1144
01:53:20,399 --> 01:53:21,398
No.

1145
01:53:22,357 --> 01:53:26,356
Will you check the situation for me
and, uh, take care of it?

1146
01:53:30,732 --> 01:53:33,064
You do like Biarritz, don't you?

1147
01:53:35,399 --> 01:53:39,064
You do like the South of France, don't you?

1148
01:53:52,399 --> 01:53:54,106
(SHELLS FIRING)

1149
01:53:56,565 --> 01:53:57,814
Come on.

1150
01:54:24,815 --> 01:54:25,981
(SOLDIER SCREAMS)

1151
01:54:26,065 --> 01:54:27,314
KERN: Oh, shit!

1152
01:54:41,107 --> 01:54:42,231
- STEINER: Kern.
- Yeah.

1153
01:54:43,232 --> 01:54:45,231
You and I will carry the weapons.

1154
01:54:47,107 --> 01:54:50,648
The rest of you make sure your hands
are clearly placed behind your heads.

1155
01:54:51,399 --> 01:54:53,356
SCHNURRBART: I'll go first, Sergeant.

1156
01:54:53,732 --> 01:54:55,814
No, Goddamit, Schnurrbart.

1157
01:54:57,232 --> 01:55:00,273
There might be some asshole
who didn't know what the message is.

1158
01:55:00,357 --> 01:55:02,314
SCHNURRBART: No, I go.

1159
01:55:02,399 --> 01:55:03,439
Rolf!

1160
01:55:07,232 --> 01:55:09,356
SCHNURRBART: You've been responsible
for all of us.

1161
01:55:10,107 --> 01:55:12,564
This time I'm responsible for you.

1162
01:55:16,232 --> 01:55:17,981
(LAUGHS) Take us in.

1163
01:55:53,607 --> 01:55:55,148
Sir, look here.

1164
01:56:28,107 --> 01:56:29,731
Welcome, Sergeant Steiner.

1165
01:56:32,065 --> 01:56:33,481
My passage home.

1166
01:56:35,565 --> 01:56:37,231
KERN: Steiner!

1167
01:56:37,315 --> 01:56:40,898
Demarcation! Steiner!

1168
01:56:41,399 --> 01:56:43,148
SCHNURRBART: Steiner, we're coming out!

1169
01:56:45,399 --> 01:56:49,148
STEINER: Demarcation!
SCHNURRBART: Demarcation!

1170
01:56:49,399 --> 01:56:51,398
Steiner's coming in!

1171
01:56:54,440 --> 01:56:56,398
STEINER: Demarcation!

1172
01:56:57,065 --> 01:56:58,981
(SHELL EXPLODING)

1173
01:56:59,065 --> 01:57:00,814
SCHNURRBART: Demarcation!

1174
01:57:01,190 --> 01:57:02,689
STEINER: Barrage!

1175
01:57:11,982 --> 01:57:13,564
Russians right in front.

1176
01:57:13,649 --> 01:57:16,023
STEINER: Schnurrbart, move out!

1177
01:57:16,899 --> 01:57:18,064
Stand by to fire.

1178
01:57:22,565 --> 01:57:23,898
STEINER: Go, go!

1179
01:57:36,482 --> 01:57:37,564
Fire!

1180
01:57:42,232 --> 01:57:43,564
(MACHINE GUN FIRING)

1181
01:57:46,857 --> 01:57:47,939
Demarcation!

1182
01:57:49,940 --> 01:57:51,731
SOLDIER: It's Steiner!

1183
01:57:54,690 --> 01:57:55,939
It's a trap. Fire!

1184
01:57:56,065 --> 01:57:57,398
(SOLDIERS SCREAMING)

1185
01:58:00,357 --> 01:58:01,398
No!

1186
01:58:02,857 --> 01:58:04,231
God damn it!

1187
01:58:06,065 --> 01:58:07,314
(SCREAMING)

1188
01:58:09,232 --> 01:58:10,689
Sir, they look like prisoners.

1189
01:58:11,190 --> 01:58:12,481
Steiner!

1190
01:58:13,690 --> 01:58:15,564
(SCREAMING)

1191
01:58:17,107 --> 01:58:18,731
There are German soldiers with them.

1192
01:58:19,399 --> 01:58:21,898
- Stop it!
- Stop it!

1193
01:58:22,149 --> 01:58:23,189
The fucking idiots.

1194
01:58:24,274 --> 01:58:25,898
(KERN SCREAMING IN PAIN)

1195
01:58:33,649 --> 01:58:35,064
We're German soldiers...

1196
01:58:35,149 --> 01:58:36,273
Fire!

1197
01:58:51,649 --> 01:58:53,023
KRÜGER: Stop it!

1198
01:59:01,357 --> 01:59:02,564
Stop it!

1199
01:59:02,732 --> 01:59:05,689
No!

1200
01:59:09,065 --> 01:59:11,273
- Keep firing!
- Stop, God damn it!

1201
01:59:12,149 --> 01:59:13,481
(KERN CONTINUES SCREAMING)

1202
01:59:13,690 --> 01:59:14,731
Fire!

1203
01:59:22,232 --> 01:59:23,481
Oh, my God!

1204
01:59:25,315 --> 01:59:26,523
It's Steiner!

1205
01:59:40,232 --> 01:59:42,064
You, stop!

1206
01:59:50,274 --> 01:59:52,356
Go get my men, go!

1207
01:59:52,440 --> 01:59:54,231
SOLDIER: Stop it!
STEINER: Stretcher-bearers.

1208
01:59:55,732 --> 01:59:57,939
KRÜGER: Bloody Nazi swine!

1209
02:00:01,065 --> 02:00:02,064
Swine!

1210
02:00:04,149 --> 02:00:06,481
TRIEBIG: It's all Stransky's orders!

1211
02:00:08,232 --> 02:00:09,898
I had no part in it.

1212
02:00:11,524 --> 02:00:12,773
We're sorry.

1213
02:00:18,607 --> 02:00:19,898
He's dead.

1214
02:00:25,149 --> 02:00:26,856
I had no part in it!

1215
02:00:34,065 --> 02:00:35,064
I'm Private Dietz, sir.

1216
02:00:48,440 --> 02:00:49,898
(SCREAMS)

1217
02:00:58,732 --> 02:00:59,939
(GROANING)

1218
02:01:21,190 --> 02:01:22,189
(SCREAMING)

1219
02:01:25,024 --> 02:01:27,064
(KRÜGER STABBING TRIEBIG)

1220
02:01:34,065 --> 02:01:35,439
(SHELLS EXPLODING)

1221
02:02:06,065 --> 02:02:07,564
You're on your own.

1222
02:02:09,232 --> 02:02:12,689
If I don't find you,
join up with another outfit, another platoon.

1223
02:02:14,399 --> 02:02:17,106
A deserter. I don't care.
It doesn't matter any more.

1224
02:02:19,190 --> 02:02:20,939
Where are you going?

1225
02:02:21,857 --> 02:02:23,439
To pay my debts.

1226
02:02:23,982 --> 02:02:28,939
You are our platoon leader!
This thing isn't over yet.

1227
02:02:34,232 --> 02:02:36,481
You're the new platoon leader.

1228
02:02:38,440 --> 02:02:40,564
And Anselm is your platoon.

1229
02:02:44,065 --> 02:02:46,356
That should make you happy, you old pirate.

1230
02:02:46,440 --> 02:02:49,064
Steiner! Steiner!

1231
02:02:52,232 --> 02:02:53,856
Steiner!

1232
02:03:06,899 --> 02:03:08,314
(SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

1233
02:03:22,274 --> 02:03:24,481
(SOLDIERS SCREAMING)

1234
02:03:32,649 --> 02:03:34,564
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING)

1235
02:03:53,357 --> 02:03:54,689
Yes, Colonel Brandt?

1236
02:03:55,232 --> 02:03:58,106
Situation is worsening here. You're needed.

1237
02:04:00,190 --> 02:04:01,856
If my orders are here...

1238
02:04:03,899 --> 02:04:04,981
And they are here, sir,

1239
02:04:05,065 --> 02:04:07,398
then my replacement is already
with the Company.

1240
02:04:07,482 --> 02:04:09,148
You may leave, Stransky.

1241
02:05:15,899 --> 02:05:18,856
Your Triebig is dead.

1242
02:05:22,232 --> 02:05:24,189
It didn't work, Captain.

1243
02:05:25,315 --> 02:05:26,731
I live.

1244
02:05:27,065 --> 02:05:28,523
You are dead.

1245
02:05:31,190 --> 02:05:34,898
Lieutenant Triebig has not been
under my command for several hours.

1246
02:05:35,899 --> 02:05:40,148
- He has been transferred.
- You aristocratic...

1247
02:05:42,065 --> 02:05:44,564
... pile of Prussian pig shit!

1248
02:06:08,065 --> 02:06:09,814
Leaving without your Iron Cross, Captain?

1249
02:06:12,232 --> 02:06:14,023
Just a matter of time.

1250
02:06:18,732 --> 02:06:20,814
Where's the rest of your platoon?

1251
02:06:27,107 --> 02:06:31,398
I said, "Where's the rest of your platoon, "
Sergeant Steiner!

1252
02:06:41,399 --> 02:06:42,731
You are...

1253
02:06:44,440 --> 02:06:46,148
Captain Stransky.

1254
02:06:49,565 --> 02:06:51,856
You are the rest of my platoon.

1255
02:07:08,940 --> 02:07:11,856
- Know how to use it?
- Yes, of course.

1256
02:07:34,857 --> 02:07:38,064
Fine, I accept.

1257
02:07:39,899 --> 02:07:42,273
I'll show you how a Prussian officer can fight.

1258
02:07:48,732 --> 02:07:50,356
And I'll show you

1259
02:07:51,774 --> 02:07:53,606
where the Iron Crosses grow.

1260
02:07:55,065 --> 02:07:57,148
(EXPLOSIONS CONTINUE)

1261
02:08:08,524 --> 02:08:10,064
(SOLDIERS SHOUTING)

1262
02:08:33,232 --> 02:08:34,314
Now!

1263
02:08:47,440 --> 02:08:49,731
SOLDIER: Hey, get out! Get out of the way!

1264
02:09:00,732 --> 02:09:02,689
(SOLDIERS SCREAMING)

1265
02:09:06,649 --> 02:09:07,981
(SCREAMING)

1266
02:09:17,732 --> 02:09:18,856
Stop there!

1267
02:09:22,190 --> 02:09:23,356
Advance with me.

